<br>
This is mainly an assumption gained from what I have seen.<br>
<br>
Many people have given up things they have on other servers to come here.  Many.  A great many.  Myself included.<br>
<br>
The attitude of those people is such that since they already gave up what they had to come here, they do not see the NEED for items on other servers.  It's like Test.  Once you come here, you most likely won't go back.<br>
<br>
The first ramification from this is that it's going to be very hard to find someone to transfer, but given enough time and the fact that I have seen people go back, the probability that you will find someone willing to engage in the trade will approach 1.  You will find someone.<br>
<br>
Anyway, digression over.<br>
<br>
As far of the opinion of cross-server trades...I'm sensing that people feel that it's taboo.  Even if you DID come here during the first few days (I started one week after it opened), you have &quot;given up&quot; that amassed time/wealth/xp on your other character.  Trying to now use what you have already given up in order to advance your character on here is essentially no better than e-bay in this sense:<br>
<br>
You are using a source of wealth/income etc, that is not Time Spent On or Native Norrathian Platinum to Firiona Vie in order to advance yourself here.  Although essentially what it is is &quot;gift-giving&quot; on both sides, since all the trades from the standpoint on ONE server are one-sided, and no money crosses the boundary between servers, you are still using something you didn't earn here to get something here.<br>
<br>
That make it any clearer, or did I cloud it further? <p>--Captain Antoin Nolouj<br>
Shadowknight of 54 Opponents, 4 Mutations<br>
